ANTIPHON
-
~The sun was coming down in the city
~I walked into a shop of toys
~I did not come here for a meeting
~I came because I heard a weird noise
~I lived across the street and saw this place
~"A shop of curiosities" it was called
~I always wanted to come and have a taste
~But never until today could be so bold
~I saw a colourful drawing in a jar
~I saw a wooden ship with iron men
~Rails with a train, a road with a car
~And a book about an unexplored land
